00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:38,696
I can't believe
Sunako's in that room!

561
00:20:38,696 --> 00:20:40,322
Oh, no, Sunako.

562
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:42,533
Did you really let
your Dad see your room?

563
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:43,576
Mm‐hmm.

564
00:20:43,576 --> 00:20:45,286
I've been keeping it
secret from him

565
00:20:45,286 --> 00:20:47,788
for so long,
but oh well.

566
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,039
Huh?

567
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:50,499
Now, listen, son.

568
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:51,792
"Listen, son"?

569
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:52,835
He said "son."

570
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:53,878
He sure did.

571
00:20:53,878 --> 00:20:55,212
Just please...

572
00:20:55,212 --> 00:20:58,466
make sure my daughter's
a decent girl, promise?

573
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:00,801
Stop butting into
other people's business.

574
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:01,802
You stay out of it.

575
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,637
She's interested
in that stuff.

576
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:05,139
(whimpers)

577
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:07,349
But...but...

578
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:08,851
Bye, Sunako.

579
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:10,728
I'll visit with
you longer next time.

580
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:11,729
Okay.

581
00:21:11,729 --> 00:21:13,397
Well, goodbye,
you beautiful boys!

582
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:14,273
(together)
Goodbye!

583
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,900
Please come back
again soon!

584
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,610
All right, then.

585
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,779
Come on, honey,
time to go!

586
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,739
(together)
Gah!

587
00:21:23,365 --> 00:21:26,076
Young man,
I'm counting on you!

588
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:27,411
On you!

589
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:28,329
Awesome.

590
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:30,247
They sure are
unique parents.

591
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:32,208
And there's certainly
no doubt that Sunako's

592
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:33,417
their daughter.

593
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:34,543
So, that means...

594
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:37,463
Sunako's going to look like
her mom when she grows up.

595
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:39,924
Is that all you
care about, Ranmaru?

596
00:21:39,924 --> 00:21:40,966
Hmm.

597
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:45,554
♪

598
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:46,889
What a nice family.

599
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:50,100
Yeah.

600
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,852
Sunako, what are your
mother's measurements?

601
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:53,521
And what is her favorite food?

602
00:21:53,521 --> 00:21:54,897
Knock it off already.

603
00:21:54,897 --> 00:21:56,607
(chuckles)

604
00:21:56,607 --> 00:21:58,067
Hmph.

605
00:21:58,067 --> 00:22:00,069
♪

606
00:22:00,069 --> 00:22:01,570
But if your mother
is that gorgeous,

607
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,614
then when you grow up,
you'll also be‐‐

608
00:22:03,614 --> 00:22:05,366
Why do you sound like
you're bidding on her?

609
00:22:05,366 --> 00:22:06,367
Well, I'm just‐‐

610
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:07,535
I have my heart
set on Noi.

611
00:22:07,535 --> 00:22:08,911
Did you say something?

612
00:22:08,911 --> 00:22:10,287
(laughs)

613
00:22:10,287 --> 00:22:11,747
My love!

614
00:22:11,747 --> 00:23:39,627
♪

615
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,216
It looks like people from
some kind of sect are coming!

616
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:47,426
I'm scared of
people like that!

617
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:48,802
I don't like those
kind of people!

618
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:50,012
What's "some kind of sect"?

619
00:23:50,012 --> 00:23:51,847
‐We can't tell you.
‐I'm being kidnapped.

620
00:23:51,847 --> 00:23:53,849
Save me, please rescue me
from the people of this sect!

621
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:54,892
What's "some sect"?

622
00:23:54,892 --> 00:23:56,018
(together)
We can't tell you!

623
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:57,061
It's grown up business.

624
00:23:57,061 --> 00:23:58,604
I'm asking you what
kind of sect it is!

625
00:23:58,604 --> 00:24:00,814
Next time on The Wallflower,
"A Prince in Sheep's Clothing."

626
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:03,317
‐A sheep prince?
‐Mine isn't wearing any clothes.

